Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
checkTQuantusModelFile(25.10)                    checkTQuantusModelFile(25.10)

Name
       checkTQuantusModelFile

Syntax
       checkTQuantusModelFile

       [-help]

       Checks  the  TQuantus  model  file created using the createTQuantusMod-
       elFile command. It ensures that the TQuantus model file  is  consistent
       with the following input files inside the Innovus database:

              * QRC techfiles

              * Pitch information from the technology LEF file

              * RC corners

       The  following  commands invoke this command automatically to check the
       consistency of the TQuantus model file if TQuantus is chosen as the ex-
       traction engine.

              * routeDesign -trackOpt

              * optDesign -postRoute

              * timeDesign

              * extractRC

       Note: The software issues warnings if inconsistencies are detected  be-
       tween the TQuantus file and the RC corner information, QRC techfile, or
       pitch  information in the LEF technology file. If such warnings are is-
       sued, the TQuantus model file will have to be re-generated manually.

Parameter
       -help  Outputs a brief description of the checkTQuantusModelFile  para-
              meter.  For  a  detailed description of the command, use the man
              command: man checkTQuantusModelFile.

Example
              * The following commands create the RC model data and  store  it
                in  the  tQuantus_model.bin  file  and then check the TQuantus
                model file:

                createTQuantusModelFile -file tQuantus_model.bin

                checkTQuantusModelFile

